<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54121s"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54121s">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54121s"> 121(s)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> X sends pig to K, not at / home, must visit, not at home <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54121s"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">He <font color="green">[Yang Hoo]</font> <mark>sent a present of a roast pig</mark>, being careful to see that it arrived at a time when <mark>Master Kung was out</mark>, and therefore unable to personally receive the gift and return his thanks by the messenger. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Master Kung knew he had been tricked and decided to pay the trickster back in his own coin. When he set out to pay his <mark>duty call</mark> he selected a time when he knew that Yang Hoo <mark>would not be at home</mark>. But the host returned unexpectedly and the scholar could not escape the interview he had tried so hard to avoid. <small> Carl Crow, <a name="CCMK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CCMK"><cite title="source">Master Kung. The Story of Confucius</cite></a> (Sep 1937) 144</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
